## MIXA-015 Complete

**Task**: Implement auto-summarization and auto-tagging

**Files created:**
- `packages/ai-pipeline/src/summarizer.ts` — Core `summarizeAndTag()` function that sends content to the cheapest available LLM (gpt-4o-mini, claude-3-haiku, etc.) with a structured JSON prompt for summary + tags. Gracefully returns `null` on failure.
- `packages/ai-pipeline/src/tag-normalizer.ts` — Tag normalization pipeline: lowercase, special char removal, hyphen-separation, bigram similarity deduplication, score clamping, and max tag limiting.
- `packages/ai-pipeline/src/summarize-queue.ts` — BullMQ queue (`mixa:summarize`) with `createSummarizeQueue`, `createSummarizeWorker`, and `enqueueSummarizeJob` — designed to run after embedding jobs complete.
- `packages/ai-pipeline/src/summarizer.test.ts` — 10 tests covering happy path, code fences, empty content, LLM failures, invalid JSON, truncation, title inclusion, and missing score defaults.
- `packages/ai-pipeline/src/tag-normalizer.test.ts` — 18 tests covering normalization, deduplication, similarity merging, score clamping, and edge cases.

**All acceptance criteria met:**
- Summarize+tag job runs after embedding via BullMQ queue
- Summary is 2-3 sentences, stored in `items.summary`
- Tags are 3-7 topic labels with confidence scores (0-1)
- Well-structured LLM prompt outputs JSON with summary + tags
- Tags normalized (lowercase, deduplicated, similar tags merged)
- Works with all providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, Gemini)
- Graceful degradation: returns null on failure
- 28 new unit tests for tag normalization and summarization
- Cost-efficient: uses cheapest model per provider

**Backpressure: All gates pass** (typecheck, lint, 96 ai-pipeline tests, full build, Go vet + test)